Guillaume,

 

I work in Tudor’s Legal and Compliance department – unfortunately I wasn’t included in any calls you may have had with the traders to discuss this product.  There’s also a possibility you’re confusing me with Chelsea Scala who works on our market services team.  As an SEC registrant, Tudor is required to perform due diligence on all external data and research providers to rule out the possibility that we are ingesting content that could violate securities laws, privacy laws, could infringe on another party’s IP, among other concerns.

 

I’m asking you these questions because if we were to be examined by our regulators (namely the SEC) they would expect us to demonstrate a clear understanding of the content we’re buying, as well as how it is derived. 

 

I think it might make sense to have a short call to tie up the loose ends around how your product is derived.  Are you free between 10am-5pm ET tomorrow (Thursday 7/10) or 9:30am-3pm ET on Friday 7/11?

 

Thank you and kind regards,

Chelsea L.

From: Guillaume Goudy <guillaume.goudy@dnext.io <mailto:guillaume.goudy@dnext.io> >
Sent: Wednesday, May 7, 2025 10:08 PM
To: Patrick Doherty <patrick.doherty@tudor.com <mailto:patrick.doherty@tudor.com> >
Cc: Brandon Bates <Brandon.Bates@xantium.com <mailto:Brandon.Bates@xantium.com> >
Subject: RE: DNEXT service

 

Dear Patrick,

 

Sorry for my delayed response but i was traveling and missed your email.

If i understand well, you are not interested in our forecast but just historical data collection such as customs, lineups, SND? And access to them via an API?

We can do things a la carte but just want to make sure i understood correctly.

Thank you and look forward to hearing from you soon.

Best Regards,

Guillaume

 

From: Patrick Doherty <patrick.doherty@tudor.com <mailto:patrick.doherty@tudor.com> >
Sent: Tuesday, 29 April 2025 11:29
To: Guillaume Goudy <guillaume.goudy@dnext.io <mailto:guillaume.goudy@dnext.io> >
Cc: Brandon Bates <Brandon.Bates@xantium.com <mailto:Brandon.Bates@xantium.com> >
Subject: RE: DNEXT service

 

Dear Guillaume,

 

Thank you for the meeting yesterday, it was great to learn about what DNEXT offers and the firm itself.

 

I am afraid that a package deal is not economically viable for us. We are primarily seeking API access / excel files to a limited set of historical time series data on country-level balance data, and global balance data.

 

As our focus is on back-testing trading strategies, we won’t need the forecasting services included in your package. Additionally, analyst meetings, while valuable, aren’t required for our quantitative approach.

 

Would you be willing to offer these specific data services on a more ‘a la carte’ basis? We would be interested in pricing for just the API access to these particular datasets.

 

Thank you for your consideration,

Paddy

 

From: Guillaume Goudy <guillaume.goudy@dnext.io <mailto:guillaume.goudy@dnext.io> >
Sent: Monday, April 28, 2025 5:31 PM
To: Patrick Doherty <patrick.doherty@tudor.com <mailto:patrick.doherty@tudor.com> >
Subject: DNEXT service

 

Dear Patrick,

 

Thank you for your time today. Please find below our offer.

 

Sugar:

1.	Platform (freight price + curve, weather, tradeflow, production, snd and forecast) + reports with historical: CHF 50k/year

 

What are the benefits of working with DNEXT?

a.   You can automatically collect information from websites, emails, or other formats. Data will be ingested, structured, and stored in a database for reuse, API access. This includes weather, statistics, port lineups or any information that could be of use.

b.   The network we have built and continue to build will allow your traders to have access to market research as if they were sitting in a large, physical trading house with a global reach but without the overheads and assets to manage.

c.   You will have access to an interactive platform with all the information you need. Your team can focus on analysis and risk management and less on data crunching.

d.   You will have access to a team of experienced trade analysts covering most agriculture commodities and benefiting from the synergies among them.  

 

Let me know if you need anything or if you have any questions.

We look forward to hearing from you soon.

Best Regards,

Guillaume

'

<p class="MsoNormal"> <o:p></o:p></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.0pt">Thank you, Sami.  This was very helpful.  As a last step, can you please provide more detail around Dnext’s interaction with the port agents?  For example:</span><o:p></o:p></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.0pt"> </span><o:p></o:p></p>
<ol style="margin-top:0in" start="1" type="1">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="mso-list:l2 level1 lfo4"><span style="font-size:11.0pt">Are they exclusively Brazilian ports (vs. receiving ports)?</span><o:p></o:p></li></ol>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;color:#00B0F0">You made the request to get Bra sugar lineups from us. Therefore, yes, it is only about Brazil. Bra ports can be receiving ports as much as an export hub. It depends on the product. We cover
 other countries and other products but it is not the purpose of this service. Again, I am bit confused as if the question is about the service we will provide to you only or is it about Dnext lineups in general? I assume it is the first one.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
<ol style="margin-top:0in" start="2" type="1">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="mso-list:l0 level1 lfo5"><span style="font-size:11.0pt">Are port agents compensated for their participation?</span><o:p></o:p></li></ol>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;color:#00B0F0">Service against service. We help them with information and our platform in exchange to use the data after it is being anonymized.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
<ol style="margin-top:0in" start="3" type="1">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="mso-list:l9 level1 lfo6"><span style="font-size:11.0pt">What authority, if any, do port agents have to share this information?</span><o:p></o:p></li></ol>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;color:#00B0F0">They do not have to. It is a service they render.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
<ol style="margin-top:0in" start="4" type="1">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="mso-list:l7 level1 lfo7"><span style="font-size:11.0pt">Do the port agents consent for you to share this information (or derived content)?</span><o:p></o:p></li></ol>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;color:#00B0F0">Yes, the derived content which is what we will share.  </span><o:p></o:p></p>
<ol style="margin-top:0in" start="5" type="1">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="mso-list:l5 level1 lfo8"><span style="font-size:11.0pt">How many ports does this represent? A raw number, along with an estimate of the % of total ports in Brazil would be most helpful.</span><o:p></o:p></li></ol>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;color:#00B0F0">21 ports approximately. It will cover 100% of bulk sugar flow.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.0pt"> </span><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="xmsonormal" style="margin:0in"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif"> </span><o:p></o:p></p>
<p class="xmsonormal" style="margin:0in"><span style="font-size:11.0pt">Dear Patrick,</span><o:p></o:p></p>
<p class="xmsonormal" style="margin:0in"><span style="font-size:11.0pt"> </span><o:p></o:p></p>
<p class="xmsonormal" style="margin:0in"><span style="font-size:11.0pt">Thank you for your time today. Please find below our offer.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
<p class="xmsonormal" style="margin:0in"><span style="font-size:11.0pt"> </span><o:p></o:p></p>
<p class="xmsonormal" style="margin:0in"><b><u><span style="font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black">Sugar</span></u></b><b><u><span style="font-family:"Times New Roman",serif">:</span></u></b><o:p></o:p></p>
<ol style="margin-top:0in" start="1" type="1">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="color:black;mso-list:l8 level1 lfo13"><span style="font-family:"Times New Roman",serif">Platform (freight price + curve, weather, tradeflow, production, snd and forecast) + reports with historical: CHF 50k/year</span><o:p></o:p></li></ol>
<p class="xmsonormal" style="margin:0in"><span style="font-size:11.0pt"> </span><o:p></o:p></p>
<p class="xmsonormal" style="margin:0in"><span style="font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black">What are the benefits of working with DNEXT?</span><o:p></o:p></p>
<p class="xmsonormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:5.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;text-indent:.25in">
<span style="font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black">a.   You can automatically collect information from websites, emails, or other formats. Data will be ingested, structured, and stored in a database for reuse, API access. This includes weather, statistics,
 port lineups or any information that could be of use.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
<p class="xmsonormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:5.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;text-indent:.25in">
<span style="font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black">b.   The network we have built and continue to build will allow your traders to have access to market research as if they were sitting in a large, physical trading house with a global reach but without
 the overheads and assets to manage.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
<p class="xmsonormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:5.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;text-indent:.25in">
<span style="font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black">c.   You will have access to an interactive platform with all the information you need. Your team can focus on analysis and risk management and less on data crunching.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
<p class="xmsonormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:5.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;text-indent:.25in">
<span style="font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black">d.   You will have access to a team of experienced trade analysts covering most agriculture commodities and benefiting from the synergies among them.  </span><o:p></o:p></p>
<p class="xmsonormal" style="margin:0in"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif"> </span><o:p></o:p></p>
<p class="xmsonormal" style="margin:0in"><span style="font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black">Let me know if you need anything or if you have any questions.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
<p class="xmsonormal" style="margin:0in"><span style="font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black">We look forward to hearing from you soon.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
<p class="xmsonormal" style="margin:0in"><span style="font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black">Best Regards,</span><o:p></o:p></p>
<p class="xmsonormal" style="margin:0in"><span style="font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black">Guillaume</span><o:p></o:p></p>

Thank you, Sami.  This was very helpful.  As a last step, can you please provide more detail around Dnext’s interaction with the port agents?  For example:

 

1.	Are they exclusively Brazilian ports (vs. receiving ports)?

You made the request to get Bra sugar lineups from us. Therefore, yes, it is only about Brazil. Bra ports can be receiving ports as much as an export hub. It depends on the product. We cover other countries and other products but it is not the purpose of this service. Again, I am bit confused as if the question is about the service we will provide to you only or is it about Dnext lineups in general? I assume it is the first one.

2.	Are port agents compensated for their participation?

Service against service. We help them with information and our platform in exchange to use the data after it is being anonymized.

3.	What authority, if any, do port agents have to share this information?

They do not have to. It is a service they render.

4.	Do the port agents consent for you to share this information (or derived content)?

Yes, the derived content which is what we will share.  

5.	How many ports does this represent? A raw number, along with an estimate of the % of total ports in Brazil would be most helpful.

I am afraid that a package deal is not economically viable for us. We are primarily seeking API access / excel files to a limited set of historical time series data on country-level balance data, and global balance data.

 

As our focus is on back-testing trading strategies, we won’t need the forecasting services included in your package. Additionally, analyst meetings, while valuable, aren’t required for our quantitative approach.

 

Would you be willing to offer these specific data services on a more ‘a la carte’ basis? We would be interested in pricing for just the API access to these particular datasets.

 

Thank you for your consideration,

Paddy

 

From: Guillaume Goudy <guillaume.goudy@dnext.io <mailto:guillaume.goudy@dnext.io> >
Sent: Monday, April 28, 2025 5:31 PM
To: Patrick Doherty <patrick.doherty@tudor.com <mailto:patrick.doherty@tudor.com> >
Subject: DNEXT service

 

Dear Patrick,

 

Thank you for your time today. Please find below our offer.

 

Sugar:

1.	Platform (freight price + curve, weather, tradeflow, production, snd and forecast) + reports with historical: CHF 50k/year

 

What are the benefits of working with DNEXT?

a.   You can automatically collect information from websites, emails, or other formats. Data will be ingested, structured, and stored in a database for reuse, API access. This includes weather, statistics, port lineups or any information that could be of use.

b.   The network we have built and continue to build will allow your traders to have access to market research as if they were sitting in a large, physical trading house with a global reach but without the overheads and assets to manage.

c.   You will have access to an interactive platform with all the information you need. Your team can focus on analysis and risk management and less on data crunching.

d.   You will have access to a team of experienced trade analysts covering most agriculture commodities and benefiting from the synergies among them.  

 

Let me know if you need anything or if you have any questions.

We look forward to hearing from you soon.

Best Regards,

Guillaume

'

What are the benefits of working with DNEXT?

b.   The network we have built and continue to build will allow your traders to have access to market research as if they were sitting in a large, physical trading house with a global reach but without the overheads and assets to manage.

c.   You will have access to an interactive platform with all the information you need. Your team can focus on analysis and risk management and less on data crunching.

d.   You will have access to a team of experienced trade analysts covering most agriculture commodities and benefiting from the synergies among them.  

 

Let me know if you need anything or if you have any questions.

We look forward to hearing from you soon.

Best Regards,

Guillaume

Thank you for your time today. Please find below our offer.

 

Sugar:

1.	Platform (freight price + curve, weather, tradeflow, production, snd and forecast) + reports with historical: CHF 50k/year

 

What are the benefits of working with DNEXT?

a.   You can automatically collect information from websites, emails, or other formats. Data will be ingested, structured, and stored in a database for reuse, API access. This includes weather, statistics, port lineups or any information that could be of use.

b.   The network we have built and continue to build will allow your traders to have access to market research as if they were sitting in a large, physical trading house with a global reach but without the overheads and assets to manage.

c.   You will have access to an interactive platform with all the information you need. Your team can focus on analysis and risk management and less on data crunching.

d.   You will have access to a team of experienced trade analysts covering most agriculture commodities and benefiting from the synergies among them.  

 

Let me know if you need anything or if you have any questions.

We look forward to hearing from you soon.

Best Regards,

Guillaume

c.   You will have access to an interactive platform with all the information you need. Your team can focus on analysis and risk management and less on data crunching.

d.   You will have access to a team of experienced trade analysts covering most agriculture commodities and benefiting from the synergies among them.  

 

Let me know if you need anything or if you have any questions.

Service against service. We help them with information and our platform in exchange to use the data after it is being anonymized.

They do not have to. It is a service they render.

Yes, the derived content which is what we will share.

21 ports approximately. It will cover 100% of bulk sugar flow.

Guillaume,

 

I work in Tudor’s Legal and Compliance department – unfortunately I wasn’t included in any calls you may have had with the traders to discuss this product.  There’s also a possibility you’re confusing me with Chelsea Scala who works on our market services team.  As an SEC registrant, Tudor is required to perform due diligence on all external data and research providers to rule out the possibility that we are ingesting content that could violate securities laws, privacy laws, could infringe on another party’s IP, among other concerns.

 

I’m asking you these questions because if we were to be examined by our regulators (namely the SEC) they would expect us to demonstrate a clear understanding of the content we’re buying, as well as how it is derived. 

 

I think it might make sense to have a short call to tie up the loose ends around how your product is derived.  Are you free between 10am-5pm ET tomorrow (Thursday 7/10) or 9:30am-3pm ET on Friday 7/11?

 

Thank you and kind regards,

From: Patrick Doherty <patrick.doherty@tudor.com <mailto:patrick.doherty@tudor.com> >

Subject: RE: DNEXT service

 

Dear Guillaume,

 

Thank you for the meeting yesterday, it was great to learn about what DNEXT offers and the firm itself.

 

I am afraid that a package deal is not economically viable for us. We are primarily seeking API access / excel files to a limited set of historical time series data on country-level balance data, and global balance data.

 

As our focus is on back-testing trading strategies, we won’t need the forecasting services included in your package. Additionally, analyst meetings, while valuable, aren’t required for our quantitative approach.

 

Would you be willing to offer these specific data services on a more ‘a la carte’ basis? We would be interested in pricing for just the API access to these particular datasets.

 

Thank you for your consideration,

Paddy

 

From: Guillaume Goudy <guillaume.goudy@dnext.io <mailto:guillaume.goudy@dnext.io> >

Dear Patrick,

 

Thank you for your time today. Please find below our offer.

 

Sugar:

1.	Platform (freight price + curve, weather, tradeflow, production, snd and forecast) + reports with historical: CHF 50k/year

 

What are the benefits of working with DNEXT?

a.   You can automatically collect information from websites, emails, or other formats. Data will be ingested, structured, and stored in a database for reuse, API access. This includes weather, statistics, port lineups or any information that could be of use.

b.   The network we have built and continue to build will allow your traders to have access to market research as if they were sitting in a large, physical trading house with a global reach but without the overheads and assets to manage.

c.   You will have access to an interactive platform with all the information you need. Your team can focus on analysis and risk management and less on data crunching.

d.   You will have access to a team of experienced trade analysts covering most agriculture commodities and benefiting from the synergies among them.  

 

Let me know if you need anything or if you have any questions.

We look forward to hearing from you soon.

Best Regards,

Guillaume

Subject: RE: DNEXT service

 

Dear Patrick,

 

Sorry for my delayed response but i was traveling and missed your email.

If i understand well, you are not interested in our forecast but just historical data collection such as customs, lineups, SND? And access to them via an API?

We can do things a la carte but just want to make sure i understood correctly.

Thank you and look forward to hearing from you soon.

Best Regards,

Guillaume

 

From: Patrick Doherty <patrick.doherty@tudor.com>
Sent: Tuesday, 29 April 2025 11:29
To: Guillaume Goudy <guillaume.goudy@dnext.io>
Cc: Brandon Bates <Brandon.Bates@xantium.com>
Subject: RE: DNEXT service

 

Dear Guillaume,

 

Thank you for the meeting yesterday, it was great to learn about what DNEXT offers and the firm itself.

 

I am afraid that a package deal is not economically viable for us. We are primarily seeking API access / excel files to a limited set of historical time series data on country-level balance data, and global balance data.

 

As our focus is on back-testing trading strategies, we won’t need the forecasting services included in your package. Additionally, analyst meetings, while valuable, aren’t required for our quantitative approach.

 

Would you be willing to offer these specific data services on a more ‘a la carte’ basis? We would be interested in pricing for just the API access to these particular datasets.

 

Thank you for your consideration,

Paddy

 

From: Guillaume Goudy <guillaume.goudy@dnext.io>
Sent: Monday, April 28, 2025 5:31 PM
To: Patrick Doherty <patrick.doherty@tudor.com>
Subject: DNEXT service

 

Dear Patrick,

 

Thank you for your time today. Please find below our offer.

 

Sugar:

  1. Platform (freight price + curve, weather, tradeflow, production, snd and forecast) + reports with historical: CHF 50k/year

 

What are the benefits of working with DNEXT?

a.   You can automatically collect information from websites, emails, or other formats. Data will be ingested, structured, and stored in a database for reuse, API access. This includes weather, statistics, port lineups or any information that could be of use.

b.   The network we have built and continue to build will allow your traders to have access to market research as if they were sitting in a large, physical trading house with a global reach but without the overheads and assets to manage.

c.   You will have access to an interactive platform with all the information you need. Your team can focus on analysis and risk management and less on data crunching.

d.   You will have access to a team of experienced trade analysts covering most agriculture commodities and benefiting from the synergies among them.  

 

Let me know if you need anything or if you have any questions.

We look forward to hearing from you soon.

Best Regards,

Guillaume

*	Order Form

Thank you for your time today. Please find below our offer.

 

Sugar:

1.	Platform (freight price + curve, weather, tradeflow, production, snd and forecast) + reports with historical: CHF 50k/year

 

What are the benefits of working with DNEXT?

a.   You can automatically collect information from websites, emails, or other formats. Data will be ingested, structured, and stored in a database for reuse, API access. This includes weather, statistics, port lineups or any information that could be of use.

b.   The network we have built and continue to build will allow your traders to have access to market research as if they were sitting in a large, physical trading house with a global reach but without the overheads and assets to manage.

c.   You will have access to an interactive platform with all the information you need. Your team can focus on analysis and risk management and less on data crunching.

d.   You will have access to a team of experienced trade analysts covering most agriculture commodities and benefiting from the synergies among them.  

 

Let me know if you need anything or if you have any questions.

We look forward to hearing from you soon.

Best Regards,

Guillaume

Dear Patrick,

 

Thank you for your time today. Please find below our offer.

 

Sugar:

  1. Platform (freight price + curve, weather, tradeflow, production, snd and forecast) + reports with historical: CHF 50k/year

 

What are the benefits of working with DNEXT?

a.   You can automatically collect information from websites, emails, or other formats. Data will be ingested, structured, and stored in a database for reuse, API access. This includes weather, statistics, port lineups or any information that could be of use.

b.   The network we have built and continue to build will allow your traders to have access to market research as if they were sitting in a large, physical trading house with a global reach but without the overheads and assets to manage.

c.   You will have access to an interactive platform with all the information you need. Your team can focus on analysis and risk management and less on data crunching.

d.   You will have access to a team of experienced trade analysts covering most agriculture commodities and benefiting from the synergies among them.  

 

Let me know if you need anything or if you have any questions.

We look forward to hearing from you soon.

Best Regards,

Guillaume
